The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: Australias pace bowling coach Troy Cooley has been appointed as the new head coach of Cricket Australia (CA)s Centre of Excellence (COE) in Brisbane, CA announced Monday, in a media release.    
	Outgoing COE head coach, Greg Chappell has moved to the newly-created role of CA national talent manager, based in Melbourne. Cooley will continue to closely support Australias Ashes and 2011 ICC Cricket World Cup campaigns as he transitions into his new role.         
	Lahore: Mohammed Asif, who is being investigated by British police in a major spot-fixing scandal, is to celebrate his wedding this week. Asif and bride Sana Hilal signed a formal wedding contract under Islamic law in March, but a series of celebrations and receptions are due to take place in Lahore from Tuesday.         
	Paris: Sepp Blatter is promising $25,000 for Kodjovi Obilale, the goalkeeper shot and badly injured in the terror attack on Togos team bus at the Africa Cup of Nations in January.         
	New Delhi: The sports ministry Monday shot another letter to the Indian Hockey Federation, seeking clarification on its merger with IWHF and the election process for its office bearers before going into polls on Sunday.         
	New Delhi: The four dope-tainted wrestlers who were earlier named in the Commonwealth Games squad only to be replaced later will not be taken back even after the provisional suspension on them was lifted by Nada disciplinary panel, Wrestling Federation of India (WFI) said Monday.         
	Tokyo: Japanese veteran Kimiko Date Krumm rallied to beat defending champion Maria Sharapova 7-5, 3-6, 6-3 on Monday, in the first round of the Pan Pacific Open.        
	Kuala Lumpur: Making an impressive start at the ATP Malaysian Open, Indian teen Yuki Bhambri demolished fellow wild card Yew-Ming Si of Malaysia 6-2 6-0, in the first round Monday.         
	Calcutta: Top seed Sanil Jagtiani easily defeated Ushmiyo Sen Gupta 7-0 in the boys singles U-12 second round, in the Calcutta Hard Court tennis meet.         
	Calcutta: Indian Life Savings Society defeated Taldi Swimming Centre 15-6 in the Shyama Pada Goswami all-Bengal waterpolo tournament. In another game, Central Swimming Club got the better of Swi-Gym Institute 12-4.    
